Documentation.name: Decision Architect
Documentation.notes:
Decision Architect allows the documentation and tracing of architecture decisions in a user-friendly and efficient way.
Decision Architect provides five decisions views. Each view is specialized to answer a different set of stakeholder questions or to document a particular aspect of the system's design rationale.

Stereotype.name: Relationship
Stereotype.notes: Diagram to model the relationships between decisions.

Stereotype.name: Chronological
Stereotype.notes: Diagram to model the chronology of decisions.

Stereotype.name: Stakeholder Involvement
Stereotype.notes: Diagram to model the relationships between stakeholders and decisions.
